{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place sugar and mint into mixing bowl and grind <nobr>20 sec\/speed 10<\/nobr>.","Add whipping cream, milk, creme de menthe and egg yolks and cook <nobr>10 min\/195°F\/speed 2<\/nobr>.","Pour mixture into shallow freezable containers up to 1½ in. high and cover with cling wrap. Allow to cool completely before freezing for 8 hours.","Just before serving, place frozen mixture in refrigerator for 15 minutes. Meanwhile chop the chocolate.","Place chocolate into mixing bowl and chop <nobr>5 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside. Clean mixing bowl.","Remove frozen mixture from refrigerator and cut into pieces (1½ in. x 1½ in.) with a sharp knife.","Place ice cream pieces into mixing bowl and crush <nobr>15 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>. Gently stir in reserved chopped chocolate with spatula. Serve immediately or store in freezer until ready to serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["5 oz sugar","20 fresh mint leaves","6 oz heavy whipping cream","18 oz whole milk","1 oz creme de menthe","5 egg yolks","3 oz dark chocolate (70% cocoa), broken into pieces"]}],"id":"r451732","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-0zqz4s8sUSc\/XZWZQHdOt1I\/AAAAAAAAeKA\/wwSL8Rfpad4ML3k8jJF7SAiED-ycU1j3QCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_XrWdABGTz_-dmF3W.png","title":"Mint Chocolate Chip Ice Cream","publishedAt":"2019-03-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"5 g","fat":"17 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"28 g","calories":"1222 kJ \/ 292 kcal"},"usefulItems":"sharp knife, shallow freezable containers (e.g. aluminum, silicone), cling wrap, freezer, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["For a firmer consistency return the churned ice cream to the freezer for 15 minutes before serving."],"basicInfo":["easy","15m","8h 15m","8 portions"]}